  "2026-07-21T16:09:10.545Z",codex-tracker-governance,"Planning verification: the tracker now contains 1,902 items (220 open, 1,670 closed, 12 canceled). Every open item has a description, acceptance criteria, estimate, risk, confidence, and parent except the intentional root milestone. Open normalization proposes zero changes. Graph audit has 3,282 edges, zero active isolates, zero active degree-one nodes, and only 11 informational historical findings. Parent-scope dedupe has zero clusters; exact and high-confidence fuzzy scans retain only the known canceled probe lineage pm-11ag/pm-lql3/pm-crpv. Integrity and history drift are clean; build passes. The only health baselines remain five actionable unknown-author events and 276 historical terminal resolution records, both already canonically owned."
  "2026-07-21T16:59:32.409Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"Local implementation evidence 2026-07-21: compatibility seeding now accepts canonical top-level compact id and historical item.id for both task and issue fixtures while preserving exact malformed-envelope failures. Focused compatibility/context tests pass 43/43. The real published-version command against @unbrained/pm-cli@2026.7.21 completed in a clean temp project with task pm-jg3a, issue pm-gapo, validation=true, health=true, and automatic cleanup. Exact-head GitHub Gates (compat) remains required before closure."
  "2026-07-21T17:15:35.843Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"Strict release-gate compatibility evidence 2026-07-21: clean published-version fixture against 2026.7.21 passed with task pm-lbr6, issue pm-99qx, item count 2->2, validation_ok=true, health_ok=true, and no migration warnings. Full suite is exact 100/100/100/100. Awaiting only exact pushed-head GitHub Gates (compat) before closure."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T16:07:03.020Z",codex-tracker-governance,"Implementation sequence: first add a response-envelope ID extractor with explicit compact/full/malformed cases; then use it for both task and issue seeding; next run focused integration contracts and the clean published-version compatibility command; finally require the exact pushed-head GitHub compatibility job before closure."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T16:07:03.827Z",codex-tracker-governance,"Compatibility fixtures are API consumers: when a CLI intentionally makes mutation output leaner, release gates must validate semantic identifiers across every supported response envelope instead of coupling to one presentation shape."
