body: "## Evidence and scope\n\nExact-head GitHub run 29846552505, job 88688713860, failed on commit 669055d9757850cdb54da198ab18df75312192d4 with Legacy create did not return a valid task id. The same command fails locally. A clean temporary installation of @unbrained/pm-cli@2026.7.21 returns the intended compact create envelope with top-level id, status, and changed_field_count.\n\n## Root cause\n\nscripts/release/compatibility-check.mjs seedLegacyData currently extracts only taskCreate.item.id and issueCreate.item.id. That assumption became stale when pm-nilh promoted compact mutation responses. The product contract is correct; the compatibility harness must tolerate both historical full envelopes and canonical compact envelopes.\n\n## Delivery boundaries\n\nKeep compact default mutation output unchanged. Centralize or clearly isolate response-ID extraction, add compact/full/malformed regression coverage, prove the published-version compatibility path in a clean temporary project, and require the exact-head compatibility check to pass before close."
